b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Podcastle is best suited for podcast creators, audio content production, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Resemble AI, meanwhile, shines for developers building voice apps, custom voice creation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Podcastle describes itself as \"AI-powered podcast creation studio.\" Resemble AI, established in 2019, positions itself as \"Custom AI voice generator for developers.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Podcastle** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Resemble AI is a poor choice — far from it. Resemble AI excels in its own right, particularly for developers building voice apps and custom voice creation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value all-in-one podcast studio, go with Podcastle. If excellent api for developers matters more to you, Resemble AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
